3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20contacted%20experts%20about%20thank-you%20notes%2C%20I%20was%20relieved%20to%20see%20that%20those%20I%20spoke%20with%20also%20have%20a%20nuanced%20approach%20to%20thank-you%20notes.%20They%20said%20it's%20important%20that%20kids%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-practice-gratitude%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpress%20gratitude%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20less%20important%20that%20they%20do%20that%20by%20writing%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForcing%20kids%20to%20write%20a%20formal%20note%20when%20it%20feels%20like%20a%20chore%20kind%20of%20misses%20the%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmonika-roots-md-fapa-32194460%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMonika%20Roots%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20child%20psychiatrist%2C%20mom%20of%20two%2C%20and%20cofounder%20at%20Bend%20Health%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20matters%20more%20is%20helping%20them%20say%20thank%20you%20in%20a%20way%20that%20feels%20genuine%2C%20whether%20that's%20a%20quick%20video%2C%20a%20simple%20message%2C%20or%20even%20a%20drawing.%20It's%20less%20about%20the%20format%20and%20more%20about%20building%20a%20habit%20of%20gratitude%20that%20they'll%20carry%20with%20them%20as%20they%20grow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294507f73-5b5c-433e-b8b2-09d4d632450c%5C%22%3EEven%20a%20quick%20thanks%20can%20build%20a%20connection%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERoots'%20advice%20was%20music%20to%20my%20ears.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20card%20and%20cash%2C%20my%20daughter%20received%20a%20birthday%20package%20from%20her%20uncle.%20I%20took%20a%20video%20of%20her%20opening%20the%20gift%20(an%20instant-print%20camera)%20and%20snapping%20a%20photo%20with%20it%2C%20then%20quickly%20sent%20it%20to%20my%20brother.%20He%20loved%20seeing%20his%20niece's%20genuine%20joy%2C%20and%20neither%20my%20daughter%20nor%20I%20had%20to%20put%20the%20effort%20into%20writing%20a%20card%20that%20he%20would%20just%20toss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20easier%20than%20sending%20a%20card%2C%20this%20type%20of%20thank%20you%20can%20be%20just%20as%20impactful%2C%20said%20etiquette%20expert%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freshstartsregistry.com%2Fjenny%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenevieve%20Dreizen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BSimple%20Scripts%20to%20Support%20Your%20People%3A%20What%20to%20Say%20When%20You%20Don't%20Know%20What%20to%20Say.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGratitude%20builds%20connection%2C%26quot%3B%20Dreizen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20people%20feel%20seen%2C%20and%20it%20strengthens%20relationships%20over%20time.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-teach-kids-be-grateful-basic-strategies-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eact%20of%20saying%20thank%20you%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20a%20scribbled%20note%20or%20a%20phone%20call%20%E2%80%94%20teaches%20empathy%2C%20mindfulness%2C%20and%20reflection%2C%20especially%20for%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDreizen%20said%20etiquette%20should%20be%20rooted%20in%20values%2C%20not%20performance.%20If%20your%20kids%20prefer%20making%20a%20fun%20video%20or%20a%20colorful%20drawing%20to%20express%20their%20thanks%2C%20that's%20OK.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20they're%20working%20on%20something%20they're%20excited%20about%2C%20it%20may%20be%20even%20more%20appreciated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20matters%20is%20teaching%20them%20to%20acknowledge%20kindness%20in%20ways%20that%20feel%20authentic%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e6b7ea0-2535-4684-9402-1c8aaf12fa9d%5C%22%3EPrompts%20and%20snacks%20can%20help%20get%20thank-you%20notes%20done%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20parent%20who%20feels%20strongly%20about%20traditional%20thank-you%20notes%2C%20that's%20also%20fine.%20There%20are%20ways%20that%20you%20can%20make%20the%20whole%20process%20feel%20less%20like%20a%20chore%20for%20both%20you%20and%20your%20kids%2C%20like%20doing%20just%20a%20few%20cards%20at%20a%20time%2C%20having%20fun%20stationery%20and%20pens%2C%20or%20working%20on%20them%20while%20sharing%20a%20snack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOffering%20a%20prompt%20or%20script%20can%20also%20help%2C%20according%20to%20parenting%20coach%20and%20mom%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjennbrowncoaching.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJenn%20Brown%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20suggests%20a%20fill-in-the-blank%20type%20note%2C%20like%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDear%20%5BName%5D%2C%20Thank%20you%20for%20%5Bthe%20gift%20or%20gesture%5D.%20It%20really%20meant%20a%20lot%20because%20%5Bpersonal%20reason%5D.%20I%20felt%20%5Bemotion%5D%20when%20I%20opened%2Freceived%20it.%20Thanks%20again!%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20about%20getting%20every%20word%20perfect%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20helping%20them%20build%20the%20habit%20of%20expressing%20appreciation%20in%20a%20way%20that%20feels%20doable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-importance-kids-writing-thank-you-notes-gratitude-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751191501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685d620285e81483682cd0d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-importance-kids-writing-thank-you-notes-gratitude-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20parents%20still%20find%20thank-you%20notes%20important%2C%20while%20others%20don't.%20Parenting%20experts%20say%20teaching%20kids%20to%20express%20gratitude%20is%20what's%20important.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-importance-kids-writing-thank-you-notes-gratitude-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%