d%20to%20become%20in%20the%20world.%20I%20took%20my%20job%20personally%2C%20and%20I%20found%20myself%20drowning%20in%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tutoring%20center%20had%20no%20budget%20or%20staff.%20I%20was%20expected%20to%20build%20something%20from%20scratch%2C%20relying%20on%20volunteers%20on%20top%20of%20my%20full-time%20advising%20load.%20It%20wasn't%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e77a92d1-1b3d-4d56-bca5-c9179dece85c%5C%22%3EStarting%20a%20new%20life%20in%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20complaints%20about%20the%20tutoring%20center's%20limitations%20reached%20leadership.%20When%20my%20one-year%20contract%20ended%2C%20it%20wasn't%20renewed%2C%20and%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-company-layoffs-laying-off-workers-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20long%20hours%20and%20low%20pay%20had%20worn%20me%20down.%20I%20was%20making%20%2442%2C000%20a%20year%20with%20a%20master's%20degree%2C%20and%20I%20woke%20up%20anxious%20and%20in%20tears%2C%20dreading%20Monday%20mornings.%20Getting%20let%20go%20gave%20me%20the%20breathing%20room%20I%20desperately%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20six%20months%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-job-market-unemployment-benefits-part-time-workers-economy-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20temporary%20health%20insurance%2C%20I%20had%20just%20enough%20to%20survive.%20I%20decided%20to%20follow%20a%20long-held%20curiosity%3A%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f6508a4d-4f40-4406-821d-2f8218e38c38%5C%22%3EI'd%20always%20been%20drawn%20to%20Whole%20Foods%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20hot%20bar%2C%20soups%2C%20salads%2C%20and%20desserts%2C%20which%20actually%20looked%20homemade%20(because%20they%20were).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20time%20of%20my%20life%2C%20the%20stress%20of%20my%20previous%20job%2C%20the%20death%20of%20my%20mother%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdetermined-marriage-end-in-divorce-backfired-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efailing%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20contributed%20to%20significant%20weight%20gain.%20I%20decided%20to%20get%20divorced%20while%20simultaneously%20navigating%20my%20job%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20threw%20myself%20headfirst%20into%20learning%20how%20to%20heal%20my%20body%20with%20food.%20Though%20I%20once%20dreamed%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-daily-routine-google-strategic-partnerships-manager-chef-harrison-hill-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eculinary%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20couldn't%20justify%20taking%20out%20more%20debt%20on%20top%20of%20what%20I%20already%20owed%20for%20my%20master's%20degree.%20I%20sought%20out%20other%20ways%20to%20satisfy%20my%20culinary%20interests%2C%20like%20completing%20the%20ServSafe%20food%20handler%20certification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224a946cdf-b868-46d7-9bda-297b8503495e%5C%22%3EI%20took%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%20and%20applied%20for%20a%20job%20in%20the%20Whole%20Foods%20kitchen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20amassed%20a%20wealth%20of%20culinary%20knowledge%20after%20years%20of%20watching%20my%20favorite%20chefs%20on%20the%20Food%20Network%2C%20YouTube%2C%20and%20PBS.%20I%20read%20cookbooks%20like%20novels%20and%20took%20countless%20in-person%20cooking%20classes%20in%20raw%20food%20preparation%2C%20fruit%20pie%20baking%2C%20and%20making%20handmade%20pasta.%20Whole%20Foods%20took%20a%20chance%20on%20me%2C%20and%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20being%20in%20a%20professional%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20hired%20as%20a%20cook%20for%20%2412%20an%20hour.%20The%20drop%20in%20pay%20required%20me%20to%20make%20some%20adjustments%20in%20my%20lifestyle.%20I%20moved%20from%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20into%20a%20single%20rented%20room%20in%20a%20house%20that%20was%20shared%20with%20five%20other%20adults.%20I%20sold%20my%20car%2C%20couch%2C%20and%20all%20my%20other%20worldly%20belongings.%20I%20had%20no%20real%20plan%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20just%20excited%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20engaging%20an%20interest%20I%20had%20held%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20how%20to%20filet%20a%2030-inch%20salmon%2C%20perfectly%20grill%20a%20steak%20with%20crosshatch%20marks%2C%20properly%20arrange%20the%20deli%20salad%20display%20for%20visual%20appeal%2C%20and%20properly%20scrub%20down%20every%20greasy%20kitchen%20surface%20each%20night.%20My%20muscles%20ached%20in%20ways%20my%20old%20desk%20job%20never%20asked%20of%20me%2C%20but%20this%20work%20was%20creative%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ade530f-65e4-4bf0-a7ab-ec9671250e0d%5C%22%3EFinding%20my%20creative%20rhythm%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20at%20Whole%20Foods%20for%20six%20months.%20Food%20service%20moves%20fast%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20I%20wasn't%20built%20for%20that%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20something%20had%20awakened%20in%20me.%20I%20started%20teaching%20healthy%20cooking%20classes%20in%20the%20Whole%20Foods%20community%20education%20program.%20I%20watched%20people%20recreate%20those%20recipes%20at%20home%20and%20come%20back%20surprised%20by%20their%20own%20success.%20That%20joy%20sparked%20my%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20documenting%20recipes%20on%20my%20health%20blog%20and%20pitching%20food%20stories%20to%20small%20publications.%20I%20worked%20for%20a%20year%20in%20an%20after-school%20program%20teaching%20kids%20to%20cook%20healthy%20meals%20while%20learning%20STEM.%20I%20noticed%20how%20the%20kids%20were%20excited%20to%20talk%20about%20their%20country%20of%20origin%20and%20the%20foods%20they%20made%20with%20their%20mom%20at%20home%20that%20were%20similar%20to%20what%20we%20had%20prepared%20in%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20dismissed%20from%20my%20job%20at%20the%20community%20college%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20failure.%20I%20discovered%20that%20talking%20about%20food%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20science%20fed%20my%20soul%20in%20ways%20that%20teaching%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224551aa31-2490-4df0-ad84-f626808cef10%5C%22%3ETransitioning%20to%20a%20new%20life%20abroad%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20that%20the%20after-school%20program%20would%20only%20last%20for%20one%20year%2C%20so%20I%20looked%20for%20an%20opportunity%20that%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20build%20a%20career%20in%20writing%2C%20food%2C%20and%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20I%20took%20another%20leap%20of%20faith%20and%20moved%20to%20Orlando%20with%20my%20fledgling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-full-time-job-freelance-live-like-early-retiree-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efreelance%20writer%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20starting%20with%20food%20and%20then%20branching%20into%20writing%20for%20wellness%20brands%20and%20the%20tech%20industry.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20five%20years%2C%20I%20built%20a%20foundation%20for%20a%20freelance%20business%20I%20could%20take%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wrote%20blog%20posts%2C%20ebooks%2C%20white%20papers%2C%20customer%20case%20studies%2C%20and%20more.%20After%20watching%20hours%20of%20YouTube%20videos%20of%20other%20freelance%20writers%20who%20moved%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20booked%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20from%20Florida%20to%20Thailand.%20I%20was%20drawn%20to%20Thailand%20for%20its%20affordable%20living%20and%20access%20to%20traditional%20healers%20who%20could%20support%20my%20weight%20loss%20journey.%20While%20there%2C%20I%20lost%2060%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202018%2C%20I've%20lived%20in%2010%20countries%20in%20Asia%2C%20Europe%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Africa%2C%20and%20now%20Mexico.%20I%20continue%20to%20explore%20what%20it%20means%20to%20sustain%20vibrant%20health%20while%20building%20a%20business%20that%20blends%20