nged%20like%20clover.%3Cp%3ENanotronics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20York-based%20Nanotronics%20builds%20compact%2C%20modular%20semiconductor%20plants%20called%20%26quot%3BCubefabs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20goal%20is%20to%20improve%20chip-making%20to%20be%20more%20time%20and%20cost-efficient%2C%20enabling%20factories%20to%20run%20with%20fewer%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vision%20is%20that%20any%20region%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20or%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%20able%20to%20produce%20what%20it%20needs%20locally%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Matthew%20Putman%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%201986%20book%20%26quot%3BEngines%20of%20Creation%2C%26quot%3B%20engineer%20K.%20Eric%20Drexler%20%E2%80%94%20often%20called%20the%20godfather%20of%20nanotechnology%20%E2%80%94%20made%20a%20prediction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20coming%20era%20of%20molecular%20machines%20will%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20many%20limits%3A%20the%20limit%20of%20scarcity%2C%20the%20limit%20of%20slow%20development%2C%20the%20limit%20of%20ignorance%20enforced%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReading%20those%20words%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20when%20he%20was%2016%2C%20Matthew%20Putman%20started%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20bodies%20work%20as%20these%20little%20micro-machines%20where%20you%20have%20ribosomes%20and%20enzymes%20and%20things%20that%20are%20working%20and%20replicating%20and%20making%20things%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20our%20factories%20work%20the%20way%20that%20they've%20worked%20for%20the%20last%20hundred%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Putman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20thought%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wondered%20how%20a%20world%20would%20look%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20you%20don't%20have%20large%20assembly%20lines%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20smokestacks%2C%20you%20instead%20just%20make%20things%20so%20perfectly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Putman%20became%20fascinated%20by%20the%20possibilities%20of%20machines%20that%20are%20%26quot%3Batomically%20precise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20the%20recent%20AI%20boom%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20idea%20really%20took%20off%20with%20fabrication%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutman%2C%20now%2050%2C%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Brooklyn-based%20Nanotronics%2C%20which%20he%20cofounded%20with%20his%20father%20in%202010.%20The%20company%20started%20out%20building%20microscopes%20and%20tools%20to%20detect%20defects%20in%20semiconductors%2C%20among%20other%20materials.%20Now%2C%20it%20builds%20small%2C%20modular%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%20plants%20called%20Cubefabs.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-startups-american-fabs-ai-chip-production-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20fabs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%20are%20often%20millions%20of%20square%20feet%20in%20size%2C%20Cubefabs%20measure%20anywhere%20from%2025%2C000%20square%20feet%20for%20the%20smallest%20units%20up%20to%20about%2060%2C000%20square%20feet%20for%20a%20full-sized%20fab.%20They're%20adaptable%2C%20and%20the%20company%20says%20they%20can%20be%20assembled%20in%20under%20a%20year%20in%20most%20places%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20also%20smart%20%E2%80%94%20thanks%20to%20the%20power%20of%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20so%20they%20can%20self-monitor%20their%20production%20and%20improve%20in%20real%20time%2C%20the%20company%20said.%20And%20they're%20relatively%20cheap%2C%20costing%20a%20minimum%20of%20%2430%20to%20%2440%20million%2C%20compared%20to%20large%20fabs%20that%20can%20cost%20billions%20to%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House%20and%20pledging%20to%20reinvigorate%20US%20manufacturing%2C%20a%20new%20opening%20has%20emerged%20for%20Nanotronics%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-us-economy-growth-oecd-forecasts-inflation-jobs-incomes-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweeping%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20challenge%20companies%20that%20produce%20or%20depend%20on%20semiconductors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221059%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matthew%20Putman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685d8c9f3d5881a51c1c28f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22794%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatthew%20Putman%2C%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20Nanotronics%2C%20is%20rethinking%20chip%20fabs.%3Cp%3EBonfire%20Partners%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPutman%20says%20that%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-could-be-heading-to-the-supreme-court-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20bolster%20domestic%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20a%20wake-up%20call%20%E2%80%94%20a%20push%20to%20create%20something%20better%20than%20what%20either%20the%20US%20or%20China%20has%20done%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20video%20interview%20from%20the%20Nanotronics%20headquarters%20in%20Brooklyn%20Navy%20Yard.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20get%20this%20right%2C%20American%20innovation%20won't%20just%20protect%20our%20future%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20help%20redefine%20global%20progress%20in%20a%20way%20that%20benefits%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutman%20says%20compact%2C%20modular%20factories%20are%20exactly%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20factory%20should%20be%20incredibly%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20Putman%20said%2C%20gesturing%20to%20the%20room%20behind%20him.%20%26quot%3BEventually%2C%20it%20could%20be%20the%20size%20of%20this%20room.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e810a57-bfa7-41ab-b21f-b97bf4b1d366%5C%22%3EThe%20'Ikea%20of%20factories'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESemiconductor%20manufacturing%20has%20surged%20sin