20jobs.%20These%20rides%2C%20called%20forward-dispatch%20trips%2C%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20convenient%20ways%20for%20drivers%20to%20pick%20up%20another%20job%20and%20for%20riders%20to%20get%20into%20a%20car%20faster.%20The%20alternative%20is%20that%20riders%20might%20have%20to%20wait%20longer%2C%20and%20drivers%20might%20spend%20unpaid%20time%20searching%20for%20another%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flen-sherman.medium.com%2Fhow-uber-became-a-cash-generating-machine-ef78e7a97230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20Monday%20by%20Len%20Sherman%2C%20an%20executive%20in%20residence%20and%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20reports%20that%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20%26quot%3Bgive%20riders%20worse%20service%20at%20higher%20prices%2C%20while%20drivers%20gain%20little%20or%20none%20of%20the%20price%20premiums%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20finding%20that%20Uber%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BContrary%20to%20the%20assertion%20that%20Forward%20Dispatch%20leads%20to%20longer%20wait%20times%20and%20worse%20service%2C%20the%20purpose%20of%20this%20feature%20is%20exactly%20the%20opposite%3A%20to%20reduce%20rider%20wait%20times%20and%20improve%20reliability%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Uber%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20is%20Sherman's%20latest%20analysis%20of%20Uber's%20financial%20performance.%20He%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flen-sherman.medium.com%2Fthe-inconvenient-truths-ubers-ceo-doesn-t-want-you-to-know-2fc0cd742b24%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20criticized%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company's%20strategy%20as%20well%20as%20its%20approach%20to%20pricing%20rides%20and%20paying%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherman's%20latest%20work%20looked%20at%20data%20for%20two%20Uber%20%26quot%3Bpower%20drivers%26quot%3B%20in%20different%20states%20who%20have%20collectively%20driven%20thousands%20of%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20in%20recent%20years.%20One%20driver%20got%20about%2060%25%20of%20their%20trips%20through%20forward%20dispatches%2C%20Sherman%20said.%20For%20the%20other%2C%20the%20figure%20was%20about%2040%25%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20showed%20that%20riders%20waited%20up%20to%2060%25%20longer%20for%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20than%20for%20other%20Uber%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiders%20for%20one%20of%20the%20drivers%20waited%20an%20average%20of%20over%2011%20minutes%20between%20when%20they%20ordered%20a%20ride%20and%20when%20the%20driver%20arrived%2C%20when%20it%20was%20a%20forward-dispatch%20trip.%20The%20wait%20time%20was%20about%20seven%20minutes%20for%20other%20trips%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiders%20also%20paid%20up%20to%2011%25%20more%20on%20a%20per-mile%20basis%20for%20forward-dispatch%20trips%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%20The%20study%20doesn't%20identify%20a%20root%20cause%20for%20this%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20in%20practice%2C%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20have%20allowed%20Uber%20to%20increase%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-uber-upfront-pricing-could-be-key-to-business-turnaround-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etake%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20profits%20at%20rider%20and%20driver%20expense%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20wrote%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRiders%20are%20paying%20more%20for%20worse%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sherman%20found%20that%20the%20two%20drivers%20were%20paid%20%26quot%3Blittle%20or%20no%20more%26quot%3B%20for%20forward-dispatch%20rides%20than%20normal%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherman%20writes%20that%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bconsiderable%20variability%20in%20driving%20patterns%20and%20market%20conditions%20across%20Uber's%20pool%20of%20over%20one%20million%20US%20rideshare%20drivers%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20there%20are%20limits%20to%20studying%20a%20couple%20of%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20his%20study%20%26quot%3Bdeliberately%20focused%20on%20Uber's%20most%20important%20driver%20segment%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20drivers%20who%20work%20nearly%20full-time%20most%20weeks%20and%20have%20thousands%20of%20trips%20under%20their%20belts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20doesn't%20tell%20riders%20when%20their%20trips%20are%20being%20filled%20using%20forward%20dispatch%2C%20though%20they%20might%20be%20able%20to%20figure%20out%20what's%20going%20on%20when%20they%20see%20their%20driver%20dropping%20off%20someone%20else.%20The%20study%20said%20riders%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20cancel%20their%20trips%20when%20Uber%20tried%20to%20fill%20them%20using%20the%20technique.%20One%20of%20the%20drivers%20saw%20riders%20cancel%208%25%20of%20their%20forward-dispatch%20rides%2C%20higher%20than%20the%202%25%20for%20non-forward-dispatch%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Uber%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bforward-dispatched%20trips%20often%20result%20in%20shorter%20average%20ETAs%26quot%3B%20for%20riders%20since%20Uber%20suggests%20new%20trips%20to%20drivers%20before%20they've%20finished%20one.%20Forward-dispatch%20trips%20are%20not%20priced%20higher%20than%20other%20trips%2C%20and%20there%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20distinction%20in%20driver%20compensation%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20two%20kinds%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d01e5a6e-0453-41d9-ae59-5aae882eb116%5C%22%3EUber%20drivers%20turn%20to%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20for%20work%20security%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20drivers%2C%20saying%20yes%20to%20a%20forward-dispatch%20trip%20can%20seem%20attractive%2C%20Sherman%20said.%20Uber%20serves%20the%20potential%20trip%20to%20the%20driver%20on%20their%20phone%20as%20they%20are%20still%20driving%20a%20rider%20to%20their%20destination.%20Drivers%20worried%20about%20finding%20their%20next%20job%20might%20be%20tempted%20to%20agree%20to%20it%20without%20looking%20at%20the%20details%2C%20Sherman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20navigating%20traffic%2C%20you're%20talking%20to%20your%20current%20passenger%2C%20you're%20looking%20for%20the%20address%20of%20where%20you'll%20be%20dropping%20them%20off%2C%20then%20this%20thing%20comes%20up%2C%20and%20you've%20got%20less%20than%2010%20seconds%20to%20respond%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20chaos.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGad%20Allon%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20operations%2C%20information%2C%20and%20decisions%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School%2C%20has%20also%20found%20that%20taking%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20isn't%20the%20best%20way%20for%20Uber%20drivers%20to%20make%20money.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgadallon.substack.com%2Fp%2Fuber-is-finally-profitable-what-drove%3Futm_source%3Dpublication-search%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20Allon%20published%20last%20year%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20drivers%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20found%20that%20they%20tended%20to%20be%20better%20off%20waiting%20for%20other%20trips%20or%20checking%20other%20ride-hailing%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForward-dispatch%20trips%20represent%20a%20%26quot%3Bconundrum%26quot%3B%20for%20Uber%20drivers%2C%20Allon%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20choose%20to%20drive%20for%20Uber%20because%20they%20want%20to%20work%20with%20a%20flexible%20schedule%2C%20he%20said.%20However%2C%20the%20same%20drivers%20often%20feel%20pressure%20to%20take%20forward-dispatch%20trips%20because%20it%20means%20less%20unpaid%20time%20in%20between%20gigs%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20more%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20think%20about%20the%20next%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20Allon%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20accept%20it%2C%20you%20know%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20next.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20want%20some%20certainty%20in%20our%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20gig%20work%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aabitter%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eabitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20808-854-4501.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-forward-dispatch-trips-riders-drivers-study-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751186702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685d5913f748d8c055f4688a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-forward-dispatch-trips-riders-drivers-study-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20study%20found%20Uber%20riders%20may%20face%20longer%20wait%20times%20thanks%20to%20forward-dispatch%20trips%2C%20and%20they%20aren't%20much%20more%20profitable%20for%20drivers%2C%20either.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A71%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-forward-dispatch-trips-riders-drivers-study-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hasan%20Minhaj%20says%20he%20once%20kept%20his%20money%20in%20shoeboxes%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20wonders%20why%20he%20shouldn't%20hoard%20cash%20like%20Warren%20Buffett%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hasan%20Minhaj%20in%20June%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685c057a3d5881a51c1c0ae9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221625%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EComedian%20Hasan%20Minhaj%20once%20kept%20his%20savings%20in%20shoeboxes.%3Cp%3EEvan%20Agostini%2FInvision%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHasan%20Minhaj%20talked