ira%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftickets%2Fhow-to-buy-kendrick-lamar-tickets-concert-tour%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKendrick%20Lamar%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftickets%2Fhow-to-get-billie-eilish-concert-tickets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBillie%20Eilish%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Enough%20to%20shell%20out%20a%20third%20of%20your%20monthly%20rent%3F%20Maybe%20you%20start%20to%20get%20real%20delusional%20and%20make%20some%20weird%20choices.%20A%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20flew%20to%20Buenos%20Aires%20to%20see%20Taylor%20Swift%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tickets%20were%20much%20cheaper%20there%2C%20and%20even%20with%20the%20flight%2C%20I%20didn't%20wind%20up%20spending%20that%20much%20more%20than%20if%20I'd%20seen%20her%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollstar%2C%20a%20music%20industry%20trade%20publication%2C%20found%20the%20average%20ticket%20price%20for%20the%20top%20100%20tours%20in%202024%20was%20%24135.92.%20Prices%20have%20dipped%20slightly%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20well%20above%20where%20they%20were%20in%202019%2C%20at%20%2496.17%2C%20and%20astronomically%20higher%20than%20the%20%2425.81%20average%20in%201996.%20Prices%20for%20high-profile%2C%20in-demand%20shows%20can%20be%20eye-watering%2C%20especially%20when%20they're%20resold%20on%20secondary%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20popular%20culture%2C%20the%20line%20on%20the%20ticket%20price%20debate%20has%20become%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-wants-t0-end-key-practice-of-live-nation-entertainment-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblame%20Ticketmaster%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20The%20ticketing%20giant%2C%20which%20merged%20with%20Live%20Nation%20in%202010%2C%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20enormous%20scrutiny%2C%20including%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaylor-swift-ticketmaster-fiasco-doj-lawsuit-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20says%20it's%20a%20monopoly%20that%20should%20be%20broken%20up.%20Live%20Nation%20has%20called%20the%20DOJ's%20claims%20baseless.%20In%20an%20email%20to%20me%2C%20a%20Live%20Nation%20Entertainment%20spokesperson%20says%20the%20lawsuit%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bperformative%20attempt%20to%20grab%20headlines%20by%20asking%20for%20a%20breakup%20that%20won't%20ever%20happen%26quot%3B%20and%20denies%20the%20company%20has%20a%20monopoly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ticketmaster%20is%20only%20one%20factor.%20I%20spoke%20with%20several%20industry%20insiders%2C%20activists%2C%20artists%2C%20and%20experts%20across%20the%20music%20industry%20to%20get%20a%20deeper%20look%20at%20what's%20going%20on%20with%20ticketing%20and%20what%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20could%20fix%20it.%20It's%20not%20an%20easy%20problem%20to%20solve%2C%20and%20it's%20possible%20that%20nothing%20could%20really%20ensure%20you'll%20get%20super-affordable%20tickets%20to%20see%20your%20favorite%20artist.%20Music%20industry%20dynamics%20mean%20artists%20now%20rely%20on%20touring%20more%20heavily%20for%20their%20incomes.%20Inflation%2C%20rising%20touring%20costs%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-indicator-outlook-concerts-live-music-economy-ticket-sales-spending-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20complex%20productions%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20pushing%20prices%20up.%20Ticketmaster%20is%20not%20helping%20%E2%80%94%20but%20neither%20are%20the%20resellers%20of%20the%20world%2C%20such%20as%20StubHub%20and%20Vivid%20Seats.%20Kevin%20Erickson%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Future%20of%20Music%20Coalition%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20supports%20artists%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20while%20a%20Ticketmaster%20breakup%20would%20%26quot%3Bhave%20an%20impact%20on%20consumer-facing%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20there's%20more%20to%20it%20than%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20with%20this%20issue%20set%20is%20people%20like%20it%20when%20there's%20just%20one%20bad%20guy%2C%20and%20this%20is%20an%20issue%20where%20there%20isn't%20just%20one%20bad%20guy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20some%20amount%20of%20hope%20that%20ticket%20price%20inflation%20could%20slow%2C%20but%20chances%20are%2C%20you're%20still%20going%20to%20wind%20up%20shelling%20out%20more%20than%20you'd%20like%20to%20see%20your%20favorite%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20explain%20soaring%20ticket%20prices%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20start%20with%20the%20stuff%20that%20won't%20make%20your%20blood%20boil%20(or%20maybe%20just%20a%20little).%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20shifts%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-do-musicians-make-money-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eway%20artists%20make%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Musicians%20and%20bands%20used%20to%20put%20out%20an%20album%20and%20then%20go%20on%20the%20road%20to%20promote%20sales.%20The%20bulk%20of%20their%20cash%20came%20from%20people%20buying%20vinyl%2C%20tapes%2C%20and%20CDs.%20Now%2C%20it's%20the%20reverse%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-musicians-arent-making-money-streaming-record-labels-and-tiktok-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArtists%20don't%20make%20much%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20off%20album%20sales%20or%20streaming%20royalties%2C%20and%20so%20they're%20reliant%20on%20touring%20revenue%20instead.%20They're%20charging%20more%20for%20tickets%2C%20and%20they're%20on%20the%20road%20more%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20just%20started%20touring%20all%20the%20time.%20And%20having%20lived%20through%20all%20of%20that%2C%20that%20was%20definitely%20in%20reaction%20to%20falling%20recorded%20music%20revenues%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20Lowery%2C%20a%20musician%20who%20is%20an%20advocate%20for%20artists%20and%20is%20in%20the%20bands%20Camper%20Van%20Beethoven%20and%20Cracker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tours%20and%20concert%20dates%20have%20become%20the%20financial%20lifeblood%20of%20any%20musical%20act%2C%20they've%20also%20become%20more%20expensive.%20Thanks%20to%20inflation%2C%20operational%20and%20production%20costs%20including%20equipment%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20labor%20have%20gone%20up%2C%20as%20have%20venue%20costs.%20Plus%2C%20there's%20an%20arms%20race%20among%20artists%20to%20make%20their%20shows%20increasingly%20elaborate%2C%20with%20complex%20visuals%2C%20lighting%2C%20and%20sets.%20Audiences%20have%20come%20to%20expect%20elaborate%20productions%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20gone%20are%20the%20days%20of%20a%20singer%20sitting%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20stage%20alone%20with%20a%20guitar.%20Artists%20feel%20pressure%20to%20try%20to%20outdo%20one%20another%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20fans%20coming%20back%20and%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20age%20of%20social%20media%2C%20sell%20more%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20artist%20will%20see%20another%20artist%20do%20something%20and%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20they're%20my%20competition%2C%20so%20I've%20got%20to%20outdo%20them.'%20So%20the%20shows%20get%20bigger%20and%20bigger%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20%26quot%3B5-1%26quot%3B%20Norman%2C%20an%20industry%20veteran%20who%20has%20toured%20with%20Prince%2C%20Green%20Day%2C%20and%20Alicia%20Keys.%20Putting%20on%20a%20big%20show%20can%20generate%20social%20media%20buzz%20and%20more%20sales%2C%20Norman%20tells%20me%2C%20but%20it%20comes%20with%20a%20big%20operation.%20He's%20currently%20on%20Cyndi%20Lauper's%20farewell%20tour.%20With%20the%20support%20act%20and%20the%20truck%20and%20the%20bus%20drivers%20and%20everyone%20else%2C%20it%20entails%2080%20people%20in%20total%2C%20which%20is%20expensive%20even%20with%20their%20focus%20on%20keeping%20things%20economical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20musicians%20hit%20the%20road%2C%20the%20harsh%20reality%20of%20supply%20and%20demand%20kicks%20in.%20Artists%20and%20their%20teams%20are%20incentivized%20to%20charge%20more%20out%20of%20the%20gate%20to%20minimize%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20upfront%20price%20and%20the%20price%20that%20resellers%20offer%20(more%20on%20them%20later).%20If%20an%20act%20sells%20tickets%20for%20%2450%20on%20the%20primary%20market%20and%20some%20scalper%20flips%20them%20for%20%24200%2C%20that's%20%24150%20they're%20missing%20out%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20underprice%20your%20ticket%2C%20someone's%20going%20to%20buy%20it%20and%20put%20it%20on%20StubHub%20or%20one%20of%20these%20other%20sites%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jarred%20Arfa%2C%20the%20head%20of%20global%20music%20at%20Independent%20Artist%20Group%2C%20whose%20client%20roster%20includes%2050%20Cent%2C%20Billy%20Joel%2C%20and%20Metallica.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20just%20giving%20the%20money%20away%2C%20as%20an%20artist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOK%2C%20so%20now%20to%20the%20blood-boiling%20part%20for%20many%20readers.%20Both%20primary%20ticketers%20%E2%80%94%20think%20Ticketmaster%20and%2C%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent%2C%20SeatGeek%20%E2%80%94%20and%20secondary%20ticketers%20%E2%80%94%20StubHub%2C%20Vivid%20Seats%20%E2%80%94%20play%20roles%20in%20pushing%20prices%20up%20and%20making%20fans%20unhappy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETicketmaster%20and%20its%20parent%20company%2C%20Live%20Nation%2C%20dominate%20the%20live%20events%20industry.%20They%20are%20vertically%20integrated%20with%20arms%20in%20artist%20management%2C%20concert%20promotion%2C%20venue%20promotion%2C%20tickets%2C%20and%20more.%20It%20has%20an%20enormous%20amount%20of%20data%20on%20fans%20and%20leverage%20over%20the%20live%20events%20space%20overall.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20tickets%2C%20Live%20Nation%20controls%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20major%20venues'%20primary%20sales%20operations%2C%20and%20it's%20garnering%20an%20increasing%20share%20of%20the%20secondary%20industry%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLive%20Nation-Ticketmaster%20controls%20all%20the%20core%20business%20lines%20of%20the%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Morgan%20Harper%2C%20a%20lawyer%20at%20the%20anti-monopoly%20American%20Economic%20Liberties%20Project%2C%20adding%20that%20that's%20how%20they're%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bextort%26quot%3B%20independent%20venues%20and%20customers.%20The%20Live%20Nation%20spokesperson%20says%20that%20some%20independent%20venues%20are%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bcynically%26quot%3B%20use%20the%20DOJ%20case%20to%20stop%20Live%20Nation%20from%20competing%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenue%20managers%2C%20artists%2C%20the%20DOJ%2C%20and%20competitors%20say%20Live%20Nation's%20dominance%20compels%20acts%20and%20venues%20to%20work%20with%20it.%20If%20an%20amphitheater%20or%20club%20spurns%20selling%20on%20Ticketmaster%2C%20it%20may%20not%20get%20a%20show%20at%20all%2C%20because%20Live%20Nation%20will%20divert%20artists%20and%20events%20to%20other%20locations.%20Some%20of%20those%20same%20critics%20note%20that%20power%20gives%20Ticketmaster%20a%20lot%20of%20wiggle%20room%20for%20charging%20exorbitant%20add-on%20fees%20that%20don't%20generally%20go%20to%20the%20artist%20or%20the%20venue%20itself.%20By%20one%202018%20estimate%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fgao-18-347.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ticketing%20companies%20charged%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20ticket's%20price%20in%20fees.%20Live%20events%20platforms%20now%20have%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-in-pricing-airbnb-ticketmaster-ftc-hidden-fees-consumers-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisclose%20the%20total%20cost%20up%20front%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20fee-palooza%20for%20many%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20vertically%20integrated%20monopoly%20in%20concert%20promotion%20and%20venue%20management%20and%20ticketing%20gives%20them%20this%20sort%20of%20enormous%20wingspan.%20With%20that%20kind%20of%20market%20power%2C%20you%20can%20set%20whatever%20fees%20you%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Diana%20Moss%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20director%20of%20competition%20policy%20at%20the%20Progressive%20Policy%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETicketmaster%20also%20uses%20dynamic%20pricing%2C%20which%20means%20ticket%20prices%20fluctuate%20based%20on%20a%20show's%20popularity%20and%20fan%20demand.%20The%20company%20says%20that%20it's%20on%20the%20artists%20and%20their%20teams%20%E2%80%94%20not%20them%20%E2%80%94%20to%20implement%20the%20strategy%20and%20that%20price%20adjustments%20are%20not%20done%20by%20an%20algorithm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20price%20on%20Ticketmaster%20has%20been%20set%20by%20a%20human%20being%2C%26quot%3B%20Dan%20Wall%2C%20the%20executive%20vice%20president%20for%20corporate%20and%20regulatory%20affairs%20at%20Live%20Nation%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BTicketing%20companies%20shouldn't%20be%20changing%20these%20prices.%20We%20don't%20change%20these%20prices.%20It's%20always%20the%20artist's%20decision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDynamic%20pricing%20and%20fees%20aside%2C%20many%20observers%20note%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fticketmaster-live-nation-antitrust-no-competition-saves-fans-money-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELive%20Nation's%20dominance%3C%2Fa%3E%20gives%20it%20little%20incentive%20to%20improve.%20New%20entrants%20that%20may%20challenge%20it%20or%20create%20better%20ticketing%20methods%20can't%20get%20a%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20They%20could%20make%20fan-to-fan%20ticket%20transfers%20easier%2C%20have%20more%20dynamic%20inventory%20flows%2C%20or%20create%20different%20recommendation%20models.%20There%20are%20some%20upstarts%20out%20there%2C%20but%20they're%20generally%20small.%20Instead%2C%20the%20entire%20live%20events%20industry%20is%20sort%20of%20stuck%20with%20Live%20Nation%20and%20Ticketmaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20one%20thing%20that%20technology%20has%20not%20made%20our%20life%20easier%20about%20is%20ticketing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gary%20Witt%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20co-owner%20of%20The%20Pabst%20Theater%20Group%20in%20Milwaukee.%20%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20monopolies%20kill%20progress%2C%20and%20they%20stop%20growth%20of%20anything%20that%20has%20any%20level%20of%20creativity%20in%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20market%20may%20be%20a%20headache-inducing%20experience%20for%20artists%2C%20venues%2C%20and%20fans%2C%20but%20that%20pain%20is%20compounded%20by%20the%20secondary%20market.%20Many%20people%20have%20had%20the%20experience%20of%20going%20online%20to%20see%20all%20the%20tickets%20for%20an%20event%20almost%20immediately%20sell%20out%20on%20the%20primary%20market%20and%20suddenly%20appear%20on%20resell%20sites%20for%20exponentially%20higher%20amounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20search%20results%2C%20resale%20tickets%20often%20appear%20before%20primary%20tickets%2C%20which%20confuses%20consumers%20and%20makes%20them%20think%20prices%20are%20much%20higher.%20Stephen%20Parker%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Independent%20Venue%20Association%2C%20a%20trade%20group%2C%20shared%20a%20couple%20of%20resale%20horror%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20one%20New%20Orleans%20venue%20saw%20its%20%2410%20apiece%20tickets%20show%20up%20as%20a%20%24700%20four-pack%20online%2C%20and%20parents%20reported%20seeing%20high-priced%20resale%20tickets%20for%20a%20children's%20production%20of%20The%20Lion%20King%20in%20Illinois.%20The%20BOTS%20Act%2C%20signed%20into%20law%20in%202016%2C%20was%20supposed%20to%20prevent%20operations%20from%20scooping%20up%20tickets%20online%20en%20masse%20and%20reselling%20them%2C%20but%20it%20hasn't%20been%20that%20effective%20in%20stopping%20scalpers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20either%20hasn't%20been%20enforced%20or%20it's%20difficult%20to%20enforce%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowery%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20the%20actual%20tickets%20aren't%20even%20on%20sale%20at%20all%20when%20they%20start%20to%20show%20up%20on%20reseller%20sites.%20This%20is%20called%20speculative%20ticketing.%20People%20list%20the%20tickets%20before%20the%20day%20of%20the%20initial%20sale%2C%20hoping%20to%20flip%20them.%20In%20nightmare%20scenarios%2C%20the%20speculator%20is%20unable%20to%20get%20them%2C%20leaving%20the%20purchasers%20out%20of%20luck.%20Sometimes%20it's%20even%20scammier%3A%20The%20sections%20and%20seats%20supposedly%20for%20sale%20never%20even%20exist%2C%20or%20scalpers%20market%20the%20shows%20incorrectly.%20A%20friend%20of%20mine%20recently%20flew%20to%20a%20Formula%201%20race%20in%20Dubai%2C%20only%20to%20realize%20she'd%20gotten%20speculative%20tickets%20that%20never%20came%20through.%20The%20day%20I%20talked%20to%20Witt%2C%20he%20was%20about%20to%20launch%20tickets%20for%20a%20Widespread%20Panic%20show%20at%20one%20of%20his%20venues%20in%20Milwaukee.%20He%20bet%20me%20%E2%80%94%20correctly%20%E2%80%94%20that%20I%20could%20already%20find%20tickets%20listed%20by%20resellers%20online%2C%20for%20much%20more%20than%20their%20yet-to-be-available%20face%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20Ticketmaster%20Live%20Nation%20merger%20went%20through%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20all%20the%20problems%20that%20followed%20from%20that%20merger%2C%20we've%20just%20seen%20this%20explosive%20growth%20in%20the%20resale%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Erickson%2C%20from%20the%20Future%20of%20Music%20Coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondary%20marketplaces%20say%20they're%20injecting%20much-needed%20competition%20for%20Ticketmaster%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20really%20true%2C%20at%20least%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20primary%20market%20sales.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20competing%20with%20fans%20to%20get%20those%20tickets%2C%26quot%3B%20Erickson%20says%20of%20the%20resellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20ticket%20pricing%20problem%20is%20complicated%2C%20so%20are%20the%20potential%20solutions.%20Different%20industry%20players%20blame%20one%20another.%20StubHub%20and%20SeatGeek%20say%20Ticketmaster%20is%20the%20problem.%20Ticketmaster%20and%20Live%20Nation%20say%20their%20integration%20is%20actually%20helpful%20for%20artists%20and%20fans.%20Reasonable%20minds%20can%20also%20ask%20whether%20streamers%20such%20as%20Spotify%20are%20being%20fair%20with%20the%20payouts%20they%20give%20artists%2C%20especially%20to%20smaller%20artists%2C%20or%20whether%20record%20companies%20are%20keeping%20too%20much%20for%20themselves.%20There's%20also%20been%20a%20rabid%20demand%20for%20live%20events%20and%20in-person%20experiences%20among%20fans%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20has%20had%20a%20price-increasing%20effect%20and%20perhaps%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20up-and-coming%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20also%20takes%20away%20from%20the%20potential%20of%20people%20wanting%20to%20discover%20music%2C%20because%20they're%20basically%20spending%20what%20they%20would've%20spent%20on%20a%20family%20vacation%20to%20go%20sit%203000%20feet%20away%20from%20Taylor%20Swift%20in%20a%20football%20stadium%2C%26quot%3B%20Witt%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20acknowledged%20that%20while%20breaking%20up%20Live%20Nation%20and%20Ticketmaster%20may%20not%20be%20a%20panacea%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20step.%20It%20could%20help%20with%20innovation%20and%20bring%20costs%20down%20%E2%80%94%20when%20companies%20have%20to%20contend%20with%20one%20another%2C%20it%20generally%20forces%20them%20to%20do%20better%20on%20multiple%20fronts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20might%20just%20have%20a%20better%2C%20more%20dynamic%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Lowery%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20seems%20to%20agree.%20In%20its%20complaint%20against%20Live%20Nation%2C%20the%20DOJ%20says%20the%20company's%20conduct%20and%20contract%20exclusivity%20block%20promotions%2C%20ticketing%20competitors%2C%20and%20business%20models%20from%20emerging.%20It%20says%20it%20bars%20venues%20from%20using%20other%20ticketers%20who%20would%20%26quot%3Bcompete%20by%20offering%20the%20best%20mix%20of%20prices%2C%20fees%2C%20quality%2C%20and%20innovation%20to%20fans.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20public%20statement%20on%20the%20DOJ's%20lawsuit%2C%20Live%20Nation%20says%20the%20move%20%26quot%3Bwon't%20solve%20the%20issues%20fans%20care%20about%20relating%20to%20ticket%20prices%2C%20service%20fees%2C%20and%20access%20to%20in-demand%20shows%2C%26quot%3B%20notes%20that%20Ticketmaster's%20market%20share%20has%20declined%20since%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20saying%20that%20complaints%20about%20Ticketmaster%20dominating%20the%20ticketing%20industry%20predate%20the%20Live%20Nation%20merger%20%E2%80%94%20Pearl%20Jam%20tried%20to%20take%20it%20on%20in%20the%201990s.%20Harper%2C%20from%20the%20Economic%20Liberties%20Project%2C%20says%20that's%20why%20a%20Live%20Nation%20breakup%20is%20just%20one%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle.%20There%20are%20other%20policy%20levers%20that%20can%20be%20pulled%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20such%20as%20barring%20Ticketmaster%20from%20having%20long-term%20exclusivity%20contracts%20with%20venues%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20them%20to%20work%20with%20multiple%20ticketing%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%2C%20a%20Ticketmaster%20spokesperson%20argues%20that%20venues%20%26quot%3Bhardly%20ever%20want%20to%20have%20two%20primary%20ticketing%20companies%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20exclusivity%20gives%20them%20the%20best%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lively%20debate%20about%20what%20to%20do%20with%20secondary%20markets.%20The%20platforms%20say%20that%20they%20do%20not%20allow%20for%20speculative%20ticketing%20and%20that%20they're%20fighting%20bots%20and%20scalpers%2C%20though%20clearly%2C%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20activity%20is%20slipping%20through%20the%20cracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiving%20artists%20more%20control%20over%20how%20their%20tickets%20can%20be%20resold%20could%20be%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20Massachusetts%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20a%20law%20that%20lets%20artists%20limit%20a%20ticket's%20transferability.%20Minnesota%20bars%20tickets%20from%20being%20sold%20online%20before%20the%20tickets%20are%20actually%20available%20to%20the%20public.%20Ticketmaster%20also%20has%20a%20feature%20giving%20artists%20and%20organizers%20the%20ability%20to%20implement%20a%20face-value%20ticket%20exchange%20that%20lets%20fans%20sell%20tickets%20to%20one%20another%20if%20they%20can't%20use%20them%20but%20is%20intended%20to%20keep%20scalpers%20out.%20On%20the%20other%20end%2C%20some%20states%20have%20laws%20requiring%20unlimited%20ticket%20resales%2C%20including%20New%20York%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Connecticut.%20The%20argument%20is%20that%20fans%20should%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20with%20their%20tickets.%20In%20these%20places%2C%20there's%20not%20much%20artists%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20most%20deceptive%20things%20that%20the%20resale%20industry%20has%20done%20has%20been%20to%20try%20and%20take%20away%20artists'%20ability%20to%20protect%20their%20fans%20from%20these%20kinds%20of%20extractive%20practices%20and%20then%20done%20it%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20fans'%20right%20to%20resell%20the%20ticket%2C%26quot%3B%20Erickson%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20evidence%20that%20limiting%20reselling%20is%20effective%20in%20keeping%20prices%20under%20control.%20In%202023%2C%20The%20Cure%20went%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20squash%20dynamic%20pricing%20and%20require%20face%20value%20ticket%20exchanges.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnitolive.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FNITO-Ticket-Resale-Study.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20National%20Independent%20Talent%20Organization%20found%20that%20for%20the%20band's%20dates%20in%20California%2C%20where%20resale%20restrictions%20are%20allowed%2C%20both%20the%20number%20of%20tickets%20resold%20and%20the%20profits%20resellers%20made%20were%2090%25%20less%20than%20in%20states%20where%20restrictions%20are%20barred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20not%20everyone%20is%20on%20board%20with%20restricting%20resale%20or%20putting%20price%20caps%20on%20secondary%20tickets.%20Moss%2C%20from%20the%20Progressive%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20notes%20that%20resale%20tickets%20are%20often%20priced%20lower%20than%20primary%20tickets%2C%20balancing%20things%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20there%20to%20match%20up%20more%20fans%20with%20more%20artists%20so%20that%20they%20grow%20demand%20for%20their%20brand%20or%20for%20their%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20is%20perfectly%20acceptable%20for%20ticket%20prices%20to%20fluctuate%20above%20face%20value%20and%20below%20face%20value.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20European%20countries%20and%20some%20states%20in%20Australia%20have%20stiffer%20limits%20on%20ticket%20reselling%20and%20scalping%2C%20and%20economically%20and%20culturally%2C%20they're%20not%20as%20accustomed%20to%20dynamic%20pricing%2C%20which%20helps%20keep%20prices%20in%20check.%20But%20there%20are%20drawbacks.%20Arfa%2C%20the%20talent%20agent%2C%20says%20artists%20don't%20make%20as%20much%20money%20in%20Europe%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20less%20compelling%20to%20tour%20there.%20A%20SeatGeek%20representative%20also%20says%20that%20limiting%20reselling%20too%20strictly%20leads%20to%20more%20nefarious%20activity%20and%20fraud%20%E2%80%94%20people%20buying%20tickets%20off%20of%20some%20sketchy%20guy%20on%20the%20internet%20or%20on%20the%20corner%20outside%20the%20venue.%20A%20StubHub%20spokesperson%20echoes%20the%20argument%2C%20pointing%20to%20evidence%20in%20Europe%20and%20Australia%20that%20places%20with%20ticket%20caps%20see%20higher%20fraud%20incidences%20and%20the%202018%20GAO%20report%20that%20said%20price%20caps%20were%20difficult%20to%20enforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOddly%20enough%2C%20one%20way%20for%20resale%20prices%20to%20get%20under%20control%20could%20be%20for%20the%20original%20tickets%20to%20be%20more%20expensive%20when%20they're%20first%20for%20sale.%20It's%20hard%20to%20guess%20what%20price%20the%20market%20will%20actually%20bear%20%E2%80%94%20hence%20why%20some%20acts%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjennifer-lopez-cancels-tour-slow-ticket-sales-concerts-prices-ticketmaster-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverestimating%20interest%20in%20their%20tours%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20agents%20and%20promoters%20guess%20the%20price%20better%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20it%20may%20cut%20down%20on%20how%20far%20above%20that%20initial%20number%20resellers%20can%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Pollstar%20found%2C%20ticket%20prices%20are%20falling%20a%20bit%20this%20year.%20An%20important%20part%20of%20the%20explanation%3A%20the%20economy%20is%20rocky.%20People%20are%20anxious%20about%20tariffs%20and%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20recession.%20They're%20on%20edge%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-worried-unemployment-layoffs-recession-jobs-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20overall%20economic%2C%20political%2C%20and%20global%20instability.%20If%20you're%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-nuclear-program-response-war-risk-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econflict%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20flare-up%20in%20inflation%2C%20you%20may%20think%20twice%20about%20scooping%20up%20those%20high-priced%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20artists%20where%20they're%20quite%20not%20as%20bulletproof%2C%20%C3%A0%20la%20Taylor%20or%20Morgan%20Wallen%20or%20something%20that%20has%20such%20heat%2C%20I%20think%20those%20types%20of%20artists%20will%20need%20to%20adjust%20pricing%2C%26quot%3B%20Arfa%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20long%20as%20demand%20for%20live%20events%20and%20concerts%20remains%20high%2C%20that's%20to%20som